                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="adam_sng_2" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">(1728-92) a Scottish architect who, with his brother James (1730-94), started a new <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/neoclassical" title="neoclassical definition"><span class="ndv">neoclassical</span></a> style <span class="gloss" htag="span" hclass="gloss">(= one influenced by the styles of ancient Greece and Rome)</span> in British building and furniture design. They designed many famous houses, including <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/kenwood-house" title="Kenwood House definition"><span class="ndv">Kenwood House</span></a> and the main building of <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/edinburgh" title="Edinburgh definition"><span class="ndv">Edinburgh</span></a> University.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
